Buying Manager Job (Information Technology) Jakarta, Indonesia
Country:
Indonesia
Function:
Purchasing
Industry:
I.T.
Position type:
Permanent
Salary:
Negotiable
Created:
05 May 2014
Our client is the top online-retailer in Indonesia, created by one of the largest iconic shareholding group in e-commerce with a strong multinational presence. They deliver customers an easy access to purchase all types of products that are involved in electronics, home décor up until products from health-care to beauty just with a click of a button. This popular site are now seeking a highly – skilled professional to manage a category of products with a focal market for kids and babies. Our highly respected client is seeking a graduate with a minimal of 5 years’ experience of relevant exposure to fill the job of Buying Manager, to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia.
Main responsibilities:
The Buying Manager will be responsible for the growth of the individual category and has to have the ability to introduce new brands through the use of personal connections, networking, and an innate talent in negotiation. In this position, a large part of the time will be to maintain the existing brands, including the order of new products, maintenance of new products and products that have already been running, as well developing and maintaining key relationships with vendors and possess a strong and firm ability to negotiate price.
Requirements:
Has a min. of 5 years of experience in retail buyer with the specified category (i.e. toys/kids/babies)
Possesses solid network in main distributor and brand, and primarily with a strong name within Industry
Possesses knowledge of buying process and a progressive experience
Strong ability to negotiate with suppliers and buyers
The ability to understand, analyze and quantify the trends in the market
Dynamic, innovative and a detail-oriented individual
A natural strong ethical business sense
All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence.